{"id": 35, "ts": 1778844444.4613166, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 1, "agent": "agent_1", "message": "I want to make sure we have examined every candidate thoroughly before leaning toward any one.\n**Candidate\u202fA** \u2013 We have solid evidence of strong technical intuition (danger anticipation, complex\u2011connections insight, excellent spatial vision) and very good leadership qualities. However, we still lack any data on his calmness under pressure or how he behaves in high\u2011stress flight scenarios, which is a core requirement for long\u2011haul operations.\n**Candidate\u202fB** \u2013 He is 100\u202f% reliable and stays calm in a crisis, and he has good technical skills (weather assessment, computer proficiency). The downside is a clear pattern of grumpy, pretentious, and uncooperative behavior, including nasty remarks toward colleagues, which could erode crew cohesion.\n**Candidate\u202fC** \u2013 He makes correct decisions quickly, handles stress well, and \u201cputs concern for others above everything,\u201d creating a positive atmosphere. Yet he struggles with communication, is seen as egocentric, and is not eager to pursue further education, all of which could hinder teamwork and long\u2011term development.\n**Candidate\u202fD** \u2013 He responds adequately to unexpected events, concentrates well, solves problems extremely well, and takes responsibility seriously\u2014strong indicators of technical competence and reliability. On the flip side, he is described as moody, a loner, arrogant, and has relatively weak leadership skills, raising concerns about crew morale and cooperation. No concrete examples of his moodiness affecting crew dynamics are available, but the descriptors suggest potential risk.\nGiven the missing evidence on A\u2019s pressure handling, the interpersonal risks of B, the communication and development gaps of C, and the teamwork concerns of D, I remain undecided. I would like to hear if anyone has any positive information on **Candidate\u202fA\u2019s performance under high\u2011stress situations** or **more concrete examples of how Candidate\u202fD\u2019s moodiness/arrogance impacts crew interaction** that could shift the balance.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_1\", \"vote\": \"\"}"}
